<br>
On my very first PoH raid (aside from my solo book run) we were setting up the usual CoH break. We got a cleric camped at the west wall, but the mage died somewhere on south wall and the rest of the break group didn't even make it past the zone-in house. Second try - all dead on zone-in. Argyll tells the guild, &quot;Port me up alone.&quot; Fifteen minutes later we were starting pulls. Between that and finding the puller who got summoned to someplace on 2nd floor, I'm not sure my guild would let me sit out on a Hate raid.<br>
<br>
Many raids later, I was with another guild in Hate. They were calling reinforcements in to drop Inny. A couple groups make it in okay, then a wizard dies porting up. At this point I'm the only rogue. &quot;Ugh,&quot; I say, &quot;somebody sow me.&quot; I dragged a wizard corpse from the zone-in house to somewhere along the west wall of 2nd floor. Not 10 seconds after I get the wizard corpse back to camp, two stragglers die at zone-in. &quot;Ugh,&quot; I say, &quot;somebody refresh my sow.&quot; I get back with those two corpses and the puller dies. Seconds later, the ranger they sent to get the puller's corpse (made no sense to me either) dies. So I go get their corpses. I've a feeling the raid leader was extremely glad she let me port up late.<br>
<br>
Man, I love the Plane of Hate. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unardacofeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nardac of EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 11:39:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22771.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Saved the day..</span><hr size=1> My personal favorite has to be in the PoH also.  We were at Innorruk and pulled him.  Things are going well but then, somehow a cleric gets agro.  He gfluxed them (or whatever that spell is that knocks you across the zone) kill the whole cleric group, so essentially its over.  I run and camp out in the corner.<br>
<br>
Well at this point everyone is dead except 1 monk who dies about 5 minutes later when trying to get another monk's corpse.   So, its down to me and Inny.  <br>
<br>
Over the course of the next 30 minutes I pulled almost 60 corpses from literally under his feet.  I even got agro once, was launched across the zone but somehow with a /quit was able to get out and live.<br>
<br>
Had to be one of my favorite moments in EQ especially considering my guild leader didn't want me there since Mugn was an &quot;alt&quot; and had to show up late.  He actually sent me a tell afterwords thanking me for coming :0<br>
<br>
